5:
I can't believe Light noticed...
I suppose it's time then...
10:
I'm sorry for lying to you this
whole time...
12:
I loved this village. I loved the people
in it...
14: But I have to let it all go...
18: Huh? Gerard? Where are you going?
21: What?! How'd you know it was me?
30:
Hunh. Yeah, you're right. Maybe I
recognized your voice or something.
32:
Actually, now that you mention it...
Why IS your armor off?
34: You know the answer to that...
37:
I do? ...Mm? Hey, now that I've gotten a
good look at your face... You're actually
pretty young, Gerard! You're like,
maybe, a few years older than me?
41:
*sniff* *sniffle* WAAAH! Oh, Alk!
Can you ever, EVER forgive me?
47:
A long time ago, there lived a farmer's
second son. He grew up in a poor little
village, and had nary a penny to his
name.
49:
We're, uh... talking about you,
right, Gerard?
52:
One day, the farmer's son met a knight
in the woods.
55:
We're talking about YOU, RIGHT,
GERARD?!
58:
The knight was sorely wounded.
It was clear that, before much time
passed, death would come and take
him.
62:
The knight told the farmer's son to take
his lance, armor, and name.
63:
He would pose as the knight returning
from the underworld. He would not
have to fight, or even say a word. His
presence alone would have the knight's
foes trembling in fear.
67:
On that day, one Gerard of the house of
Martel died... And a new one was born.
72:
Epic?! What's epic about taking
someone's armor and playing knight?!
What's epic about lying?!
74:
I haven't a drop of noble blood in me!
My family's been farmers for
generations! I'm a sham, and
nothing more!
77:
Blood? What does blood have do with
anything?
80:
Well, er... Only nobles can become
knights, you know.
91:
"A true knight has arms of steel, and
a heart of gold!"
94:
What else do you always say?
"A true knight stands firm, even before
the very jaws of death!"
96:
You've said a lot of things about
knights... But I don't remember a single
quote about blood or nobles
or anything.
105:
Gerard too! We received a message
from the Guild. Monsters have
managed to slip into town.
107:
The people of Papebra are in danger!
We must go to their aid!
116:
"A true knight is a bulwark
to the people!"
118:
I am Gerard of the house of Martel!
I am a friend to the weak, and a light in
the dark!
I am all that a knight should be!
120:
And I am terribly sorry, Alk... I nearly
strayed from my path, but the peril
has passed!
124:
Great! I don't get why you're
apologizing, but we really have go!
128:
(O brave Sir Knight... No... Comrade,
friend. Hear me now.)
129:
(From this moment onwards, I dedicate
your lance... and my life... to protecting
the innocent.)
